## Summary

Added two new functions to `pkg/display/display.go`:

1. **`VisualWidth(s string) int`** — Returns the visual display width of a string, correctly handling:
   - ANSI escape codes (stripped via existing `StripANSI`)
   - Unicode characters (CJK, emoji)
   - Counted as runes, not bytes

2. **`PadToWidth(s string, width int) string`** — Right-pads strings to reach target visual width while:
   - Preserving ANSI codes
   - Ignoring ANSI codes in width calculation
   - Returning unchanged if already at/wider than target

## Test Coverage

Added comprehensive tests covering:
- Plain ASCII strings
- ANSI color codes (single and combined)
- Unicode (Chinese characters, emoji)
- ANSI + Unicode combinations
- Edge cases (empty strings, already at width, wider than target)

✅ All 8 tests pass (6 existing + 2 new)

